#. type: Content of: <guide><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-administration-p2.xml:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "LPI certification 101 (release 2) exam prep, Part 2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-administration-p2.xml:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In this tutorial, you will learn how to use regular expressions to search files\n"
"for text patterns, how to locate files on your system, and how to take full\n"
"control of Linux processes. You'll even get a whirlwind introduction to shell\n"
"pipelines, redirection, and text processing commands. By the end of this\n"
"tutorial, you'll have a solid grounding in basic Linux administration and will\n"
"be ready to begin learning more advanced Linux system administration skills in\n"
"the follow-on tutorial.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-administration-p2.xml:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before You Start"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-administration-p2.xml:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "About this tutorial"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-administration-p2.xml:46
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Welcome to \"Basic administration,\" the second of four tutorials designed to\n"
"prepare you for the Linux Professional Institute's 101 exam. In this tutorial,\n"
"we'll show you how to use regular expressions to search files for text\n"
"patterns. Next, we'll introduce you to the Filesystem Hierarchy Standard (FSH),\n"
"and then show you how to locate files on your system. Then, we'll show you how\n"
"to take full control of Linux processes by running them in the background,\n"
"listing processes, detaching processes from the terminal, and more. Next, we'll\n"
"give you a whirlwind introduction to shell pipelines, redirection, and text\n"
"processing commands. Finally, we'll introduce you to Linux kernel modules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-administration-p2.xml:58
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This particular tutorial (Part 2) is ideal for those who have a good basic\n"
"knowledge of bash and want to receive a solid introduction to basic Linux\n"
"administration tasks. If you are new to Linux, we recommend that you complete\n"
"Part 1 of this tutorial series first before continuing. For some, much of this\n"
"material will be new, but more experienced Linux users may find this tutorial\n"
"to be a great way of \"rounding out\" their basic Linux administration skills.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-administration-p2.xml:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For those who have taken the release 1 version of this tutorial for reasons\n"
"other than LPI exam preparation, you probably don't need to take this one.\n"
"However, if you do plan to take the exams, you should strongly consider reading\n"
"this revised tutorial.\n"
msgstr ""

